---
import acornWordmark from './public/acorn-wordmark.png';
import favicon from './public/favicon.jpeg';
---
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <link rel="icon" type="image/jpeg" href={favicon.src} />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>Acorn | Sovereign AI for 7-Figure Founders</title>
        <script is:inline>
            document.documentElement.classList.add('is-loaded');
        </script>
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500;600&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <nav class="site-header">
            <div class="shell nav-inner">
                <a href="/" class="nav-logo" aria-label="Acorn home">
                    <img src={acornWordmark.src} alt="Acorn Rooted Intelligence" />
                </a>

                <a href="#waitlist" class="nav-btn">Join the Waitlist</a>
            </div>
        </nav>

        <main>
            <section class="hero">
                <div class="shell hero-inner">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Humans orient. Agents execute. Trust is earned.</p>
                    <h1 class="hero-triad">The power of Claude.<br />The simplicity of Slack.<br />The ownership of open source.</h1>
                    <p class="hero-sub">Acorn is the AI chief of staff for seven-figure founders. It lives in Slack. It runs on your own server. It gets oriented on how you run your business, and that orientation stays on your disk.</p>
                    <div class="hero-buttons">
                        <a href="#waitlist" class="btn-primary">Join the waitlist</a>
                    </div>
                    <p class="hero-note">Built by a fractional COO, for founders.</p>
                    <div class="metric-strip" aria-label="Acorn operating system attributes">
                        <div><span>Private Memory</span><strong>Your Amazon server</strong><small>Retains context across conversations.</small></div>
                        <div><span>Interface</span><strong>Slack-native</strong><small>Works inside your team rhythm.</small></div>
                        <div><span>Execution</span><strong>You approve actions</strong><small>Authority expands only when earned.</small></div>
                        <div><span>Permissions</span><strong>You choose who sees what</strong><small>Your infrastructure. Your rules.</small></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-wave" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            </section>

            <section class="options section-pad">
                <div class="shell options-inner">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Your three options today</p>
                    <h2>Today, a founder who wants serious AI has three options.</h2>
                    <div class="options-grid">
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">Option 01</span>
                            <h3>Hand everything to Claude.</h3>
                            <p>It's powerful. But your context gets stuck inside their projects. You start over. You cross your fingers.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">Option 02</span>
                            <h3>Buy a vendor app.</h3>
                            <p>Easy to use. "Customized for you." And they keep the keys: your data, your files, your process. The meter never stops.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">Option 03</span>
                            <h3>Go open source.</h3>
                            <p>You own everything. Congratulations, you're a tech bro now. You'll study every week just to keep up, while your real business waits.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card fourth-option">
                            <span class="trust-level">The fourth option</span>
                            <h3>Acorn is the fourth option.</h3>
                            <p>The power of Claude. The simplicity of Slack. The ownership of open source. Priced for a seven-figure company. One flat price, living on your server, using your compute keys, with no surprises. And if you ever cancel, the software keeps working, because it's already on your box.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="context-map section-pad">
                <div class="shell map-grid">
                    <div class="map-copy">
                        <p class="eyebrow">CONTEXT SYSTEM</p>
                        <h2>How Acorn Builds Context</h2>
                        <p>Connect the systems that already carry your business context. Acorn turns those signals into private operating memory, then routes the right work back into your team rhythm.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="map-card architecture-system" aria-label="Context architecture diagram">
                        <div class="context-column">
                            <span class="map-group-label">Inputs</span>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Slack</strong><small>Team signal</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Email</strong><small>Client context</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Drive</strong><small>Business docs</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>mcps</strong><small>Approved systems</small></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
                        <div class="map-core">
                            <strong>Acorn</strong>
                            <small>Private Business Context</small>
                            <em>Orientation layer active</em>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
                        <div class="context-column">
                            <span class="map-group-label">Outputs</span>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Decisions</strong><small>With context</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Drafts</strong><small>In your voice</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Follow-ups</strong><small>No dropped threads</small></div>
                            <div class="map-node"><strong>Priorities</strong><small>Weekly focus</small></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="orientation section-pad">
                <div class="shell editorial-card">
                    <div class="orient-copy">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Orientation</p>
                        <h2>Acorn gets oriented on you.</h2>
                        <p>The vendor apps customize their tool for you, and they keep the keys. Open source lets you customize everything, if you do the work. Claude gives you projects, and you start over in every one.</p>
                        <p>Acorn gets oriented on you. What you believe. How you decide. How you've done this the last fifty times. What winning looks like for your company.</p>
                        <p>That orientation lives in files on your own server. What humans said is write-protected: the AI cannot rewrite the record. Every answer can show its source.</p>
                        <p>Orientation is the product. Everything else is execution.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="orientation-steps" aria-label="OODA loop">
                        <article class="orientation-card">
                            <h3>Observe</h3>
                            <p>Read the terrain.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="orientation-card orient">
                            <h3>Orient</h3>
                            <p>Understand what matters.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="orientation-card">
                            <h3>Decide</h3>
                            <p>Choose the right move.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="orientation-card">
                            <h3>Act</h3>
                            <p>Execute with judgment.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="seven section-pad">
                <div class="shell seven-inner">
                    <p class="eyebrow">What Acorn does for you</p>
                    <h2>Seven things Acorn does for you.</h2>
                    <div class="seven-grid">
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">01</span>
                            <h3>Know what's happening in your company.</h3>
                            <p>You're busy. Things slip past you. You find out late, or by accident. I asked my own Acorn about a company I only give two hours a week. It listed what happened. My reaction, three times in a row: "I didn't know that." And I'm the owner.</p>
                            <p>Ask Acorn what happened last week. Ask what to focus on this week. It answers from the record, with the specific three things. "The point of Acorn is not to let AI do everything for you. It's so you better know what's happening in your company."</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">02</span>
                            <h3>Hand off the work you hate.</h3>
                            <p>Every founder has tasks that must be done perfectly but are beneath them. Data entry. Re-quoting. Purchase orders. Chasing follow-ups. You can't drop them, so they eat your week.</p>
                            <p>Acorn takes the most frustrating and annoying tasks off your plate: the ones that must be done right every time and drain you the most. You go from doing the work to checking the work. That's how your company acts like it's ten times the size, with the same people.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">03</span>
                            <h3>Stop checking the AI's math.</h3>
                            <p>AI is never going to be more than 95% correct. It always needs some hand-holding. In my experience, working straight in Claude or Grok gets you about 80% right, and you have to double-check all of it.</p>
                            <p>Acorn uses three brains (Claude, Grok, and Gemini) that check each other, working on files that live on your server. What I'm seeing is closer to 95%. And the last 5% comes to you on purpose: Acorn acts on the routine, proposes on the judgment calls, and escalates the weird stuff.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">04</span>
                            <h3>It remembers what you said.</h3>
                            <p>You know this fight. The AI says you decided something. You say, "No, I didn't say that. You said that." It says, "Oh, you're right, I'm sorry." Then it does it again.</p>
                            <p>In Acorn, what humans said is saved in files the AI cannot rewrite. Every answer has to show its source. You got a link for that? It does. And with three brains watching each other, it lies less, because there's a record on disk.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">05</span>
                            <h3>Get answers made for you.</h3>
                            <p>Claude, Grok, and Gemini speak to the average person. That's regression to the mean, in every single conversation. You built a seven-figure company. You're the opposite of average, and your customers are too.</p>
                            <p>Acorn starts from what you believe, what winning looks like for you, and your own body of work. When it's stuck, it can ask HQ how I would handle it, backed by eight years of my calls.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">06</span>
                            <h3>Protect your context.</h3>
                            <p>Your best thinking is scattered across apps that won't hand it back. You get a good idea in the car and there's nowhere to put it that connects to the project. And when you switch tools, the pile stays behind. One founder told me she'd lose 700 conversations just moving from one Claude plan to another.</p>
                            <p>With Acorn there is one contextual spot: your server. Talk to it from anywhere you have Slack. Drop a voice memo from the car. It lands in the right place, every time, because Acorn files everything to your own disk.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card seven-wide">
                            <span class="trust-level">07</span>
                            <h3>Own your AI.</h3>
                            <p>Every other AI company bills you for usage. Credits, seats, meters. If you're paying $30 a month for AI, you're the product. They don't want to be a customer. They want to be THE customer.</p>
                            <p>Acorn bills for orientation. Your server cost and your compute go straight to Amazon and the model companies, with nothing added on. No seats: one founder or a whole team, it's one price. And if you ever cancel, the software keeps working, because it's on your server. You're never just renting your intelligence.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="meet-acorn section-pad">
                <div class="shell meet-grid">
                    <div class="meet-copy">
                        <p class="eyebrow">AGENTIC AI ARCHITECTURE</p>
                        <h2>A Chief of Staff That Understands Context</h2>
                        <p>A Chief of Staff agent that lives on your Amazon server, talks to you in Slack, and earns your trust over time.</p>
                        <div class="feature-row">
                            <span class="feature-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                            <span>Lives on your Amazon server</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="feature-row">
                            <span class="feature-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                            <span>Slack interface</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="acorn-examples" aria-label="Acorn examples">
                            <p>Acorn catches a missed follow-up.</p>
                            <p>Acorn summarizes a client thread.</p>
                            <p>Acorn flags a project risk.</p>
                            <p>Acorn drafts next week's priorities.</p>
                            <p>Acorn prepares meeting context.</p>
                            <p>Acorn identifies bottlenecks.</p>
                            <p>Acorn drafts the proposal.</p>
                            <p>Acorn surfaces the risk.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slack-card" id="acorn-demo" aria-label="Acorn Slack-style conversation">
                        <div class="slack-top">
                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>
                            <strong># founder-ops</strong>
                        </div>
                        <div class="status-stack">
                            <span>Reading #sales, #ops, and #finance</span>
                            <span>Checking last week's calls and open invoices</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chat-bubble user-bubble reveal-1">What are the top 3 things I should do this week to help the team close more?</div>
                        <div class="chat-bubble acorn-bubble reveal-2">
                            <p class="bubble-lead">Three moves from the owner's seat:</p>
                            <ol class="acorn-list">
                                <li><strong>Clear your closer's path.</strong> Two warm deals are waiting on a decision from you. A 15-minute call closes both.</li>
                                <li><strong>Give your SDR a target number.</strong> She's building the call list now. A weekly goal keeps outreach pointed at revenue.</li>
                                <li><strong>Collect the open invoices</strong> before they age past 60 days. One owner-to-owner email keeps the biggest one moving.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <p class="bubble-close">Everything else, content and pipeline, is already running. These three are where your weight moves revenue.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="sovereignty-band">
                <div class="shell sovereignty-inner">
                    <div>
                        <p class="eyebrow">Trust</p>
                        <h2>Control Without Bottlenecks.</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="security-claims">
                        <span>Runs on your Amazon server</span>
                        <span>No training on private data</span>
                        <span>You choose who sees what</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="trust section-pad">
                <div class="shell trust-inner">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Authority model</p>
                    <h2>How Trust Is Earned</h2>
                    <p class="trust-sub">Acorn earns authority the way a new hire does.</p>
                    <div class="trust-progression">
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">Level 01</span>
                            <h3>Act and Report</h3>
                            <p>Routine work inside its authority. It does the job and tells you what it did. No bottleneck. No waiting.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card featured">
                            <span class="trust-level">Level 02</span>
                            <h3>Propose and Wait</h3>
                            <p>Decisions that need your judgment. It presents options and waits for your call. Everything starts here.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="trust-card">
                            <span class="trust-level">Level 03</span>
                            <h3>Escalate</h3>
                            <p>Outside its scope, it flags it and holds. No guessing. No silent action.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                    <p class="trust-close">What humans said is saved in files the AI cannot rewrite. Every answer can show its source. Three brains check the same files. The last 5% comes to you on purpose.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="founder-presence section-pad">
                <div class="shell founder-strip">
                    <div class="founder-mark" aria-hidden="true">BK</div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="eyebrow">FOUNDER-LED BUILD</p>
                        <h2>Brian Keith is building Acorn for operators who cannot outsource judgment.</h2>
                        <blockquote>"The founder running a real business with real employees and real risk has been underserved by AI. Acorn is built for them. We're manufacturing freedom for American small businesses."</blockquote>
                        <p class="attribution">Brian Keith, Founder</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mission section-pad">
                <div class="shell editorial-card mission-card">
                    <div>
                        <p class="eyebrow">Why I'm building this</p>
                        <h2>Your business is the money engine for your mission.</h2>
                        <p>Every founder I talk to has one: the birth centers they want to fund, the industry they want to rebuild, the town they want to invest in, the family they want more time with.</p>
                        <p>Acorn exists so the engine runs with less of you inside it. Make the money. Then go do the thing you're supposed to be doing on this earth.</p>
                        <div class="hero-buttons mission-buttons">
                            <a href="#waitlist" class="btn-primary">Join the waitlist</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="deployment section-pad">
                <div class="shell deployment-inner">
                    <div>
                        <p class="eyebrow">What happens next</p>
                        <h2>What Happens Next</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="deployment-steps">
                        <article><span>01</span><strong>Join the Waitlist</strong></article>
                        <article><span>02</span><strong>Talk with Acorn architect Brian Keith</strong></article>
                        <article><span>03</span><strong>Get invited to Acorn when a space opens up</strong></article>
                        <article><span>04</span><strong>Enjoy running your business with a Chief of Staff loyal to you</strong></article>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="waitlist-wrap section-pad" id="waitlist">
                <div class="waitlist-card">
                    <p class="eyebrow">FOUNDING ACCESS</p>
                    <h2>Join the waitlist to discover Acorn for yourself</h2>
                    <p class="capacity-note">Sign up below, and you'll hear from Brian and get invited when a space opens up.</p>
                    <form accept-charset="UTF-8" action="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.com/app/form/process/8bce157b4a83074b0edda9c55e1ed0ba" class="infusion-form waitlist-form" id="inf_form_8bce157b4a83074b0edda9c55e1ed0ba" method="POST">
                        <input name="inf_form_xid" type="hidden" value="8bce157b4a83074b0edda9c55e1ed0ba" />
                        <input name="inf_thank_you" type="hidden" value="https://buyacorn.com/welcome" />
                        <input name="inf_form_name" type="hidden" value="BuyAcorn.com Waitlist" />
                        <input name="infusionsoft_version" type="hidden" value="1.70.0.942760" />
                        <input id="inf_field_Email" name="inf_field_Email" placeholder="Enter your email" type="email" required />
                        <button class="btn-primary infusion-recaptcha" id="recaptcha_8bce157b4a83074b0edda9c55e1ed0ba" type="submit">Join the waitlist</button>
                        <input type="text" name="inf-sbt" style="display:none !important;" />
                    </form>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <footer class="site-footer">
            <div class="shell footer-grid">
                <div class="footer-brand">
                    <a href="/" class="footer-logo" aria-label="Acorn home">
                        <img src={acornWordmark.src} alt="Acorn Rooted Intelligence" />
                    </a>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>Contact</h3>
                    <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>Resources</h3>
                    <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
                    <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>Founder</h3>
                    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/briankeithal/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
                    <a href="https://x.com/briankeith" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">X</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="shell footer-meta">&copy; 2026 Red Beard Consulting LLC.</div>
        </footer>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.app/app/webTracking/getTrackingCode"></script>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.com/resources/external/recaptcha/production/recaptcha.js?b=1.70.0.942760"></script>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.com/resources/external/recaptcha/production/enterpriseRecaptcha.js?b=1.70.0.942760"></script>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.com/app/timezone/timezoneInputJs?xid=8bce157b4a83074b0edda9c55e1ed0ba"></script>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.com/js/jquery/jquery-3.3.1.js"></script>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://redbeard.infusionsoft.app/app/webform/overwriteRefererJs"></script>
        <script is:inline>
            document.querySelectorAll('form').forEach((form) => {
                form.addEventListener('submit', () => {
                    form.classList.add('is-submitting');
                    const button = form.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
                    if (button) {
                        button.dataset.label = button.textContent || '';
                        button.textContent = 'Securing request...';
                    }
                });
            });

        </script>
    </body>
</html>

<style>
    :root {
        --rooted-green: #032B27;
        --signal-sage: #A9C3B1;
        --deep-green: #032B27;
        --ink-green: #021F1C;
        --surface-green: #032B27;
        --glass: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045);
        --glass-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
        --glass-border: rgba(190, 230, 200, 0.16);
        --glass-line: rgba(169, 195, 177, 0.5);
        --oak-brown: #5C4B43;
        --paper-white: #F4F2EC;
        --paper-deep: #D7DED8;
        --tech-grey: #333333;
        --muted: #B9C1BB;
        --border: rgba(190, 230, 200, 0.18);
        --white: #F4F2EC;
        --font-serif: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
        --font-sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, system-ui, sans-serif;
    }

    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }

    body {
        background: var(--ink-green);
        color: var(--tech-grey);
        font-family: var(--font-sans);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .hero-inner > *,
    .founder-strip,
    .need-card,
    .map-copy,
    .map-card,
    .editorial-card,
    .meet-copy,
    .slack-card,
    .sovereignty-inner > *,
    .trust-inner > *,
    .deployment-inner > *,
    .waitlist-card {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(18px);
    }

    .is-loaded .hero-inner > *,
    .is-loaded .founder-strip,
    .is-loaded .need-card,
    .is-loaded .map-copy,
    .is-loaded .map-card,
    .is-loaded .editorial-card,
    .is-loaded .meet-copy,
    .is-loaded .slack-card,
    .is-loaded .sovereignty-inner > *,
    .is-loaded .trust-inner > *,
    .is-loaded .deployment-inner > *,
    .is-loaded .waitlist-card {
        animation: reveal-up 720ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1) forwards;
    }

    .is-loaded .hero-inner > *:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 80ms; }
    .is-loaded .hero-inner > *:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 150ms; }
    .is-loaded .hero-inner > *:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 220ms; }
    .is-loaded .hero-inner > *:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 300ms; }

    img {
        max-width: 100%;
    }

    .shell {
        width: min(1120px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .section-pad {
        padding: 156px 0;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--rooted-green);
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: clamp(58px, 8vw, 96px);
        line-height: 0.94;
        max-width: 980px;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: clamp(42px, 5vw, 64px);
        line-height: 1.05;
    }

    h3 {
        font-size: 28px;
        line-height: 1.1;
    }

    p {
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .eyebrow {
        color: var(--signal-sage);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        line-height: 1.2;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .site-header,
    .site-footer {
        background: var(--ink-green);
        border-color: transparent;
    }

    .site-header {
        border-bottom: none;
        padding: 10px 0;
    }

    .nav-inner {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 24px;
    }

    .nav-logo {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

